Real DevOps Scenario
Problem

Users report:

"Website is down."

What should you do?

Step 1
systemctl status nginx
Step 2
journalctl -u nginx -n 50

Suppose you see:

Permission denied
Step 3

Check configuration:

sudo nginx -t
Step 4

Fix the configuration.

Step 5

Restart:

sudo systemctl restart nginx
Step 6

Confirm:

systemctl status nginx

This is a structured troubleshooting approach instead of restarting services blindly.

Biggest Mistakes Engineers Make
❌ Mistake 1

Restarting services without checking logs.

Always inspect the logs first.

❌ Mistake 2

Using cat on huge log files.

Prefer:

tail
less
grep
journalctl

These are faster and more practical.

❌ Mistake 3

Ignoring warnings.

Today's warning can become tomorrow's outage. Review recurring warnings before they escalate.

