🧠 Mentor's Pro Tip

Many new engineers think troubleshooting means restarting services. Experienced DevOps engineers follow a consistent sequence:

Understand the problem.
Check the service status (systemctl status).
Read the relevant logs (journalctl or /var/log/...).
Identify the root cause.
Apply the fix.
Verify the service and logs again.

Following this process consistently will help you solve production issues more effectively and perform well in technical interviews.